68#define LOADER_RELEASE_LOG(fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG(Network, "%p - [pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64 ", frameID=%" PRIu64 ", resourceID=%" PRIu64 ", isMainResource=%d, destination=%u, isSynchronous=%d] NetworkResourceLoader::" fmt, this, m_parameters.webPageProxyID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.webPageID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.webFrameID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.identifier, isMainResource(), static_cast<unsigned>(m_parameters.options.destination), isSynchronous(), ##__VA_ARGS__)
69#define LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Network, "%p - [pageProxyID=%" PRIu64 ", webPageID=%" PRIu64 ", frameID=%" PRIu64 ", resourceID=%" PRIu64 ", isMainResource=%d, destination=%u, isSynchronous=%d] NetworkResourceLoader::" fmt, this, m_parameters.webPageProxyID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.webPageID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.webFrameID.toUInt64(), m_parameters.identifier, isMainResource(), static_cast<unsigned>(m_parameters.options.destination), isSynchronous(), ##__VA_ARGS__)

74struct NetworkResourceLoader::SynchronousLoadData {
75 WTF_MAKE_STRUCT_FAST_ALLOCATED;
76
77 SynchronousLoadData(Messages::NetworkConnectionToWebProcess::PerformSynchronousLoad::DelayedReply&& reply)
78 : delayedReply(WTFMove(reply))
79 {
80 ASSERT(delayedReply);
81 }
82 ResourceRequest currentRequest;
83 Messages::NetworkConnectionToWebProcess::PerformSynchronousLoad::DelayedReply delayedReply;
84 ResourceResponse response;
85 ResourceError error;
86};
87
88static void sendReplyToSynchronousRequest(NetworkResourceLoader::SynchronousLoadData& data, const SharedBuffer* buffer, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
89{
90 ASSERT(data.delayedReply);
91 ASSERT(!data.response.isNull() || !data.error.isNull());
92
93 Vector<uint8_t> responseBuffer;
94 if (buffer && buffer->size())
95 responseBuffer.append(buffer->data(), buffer->size());
96
97 data.response.setDeprecatedNetworkLoadMetrics(Box<NetworkLoadMetrics>::create(metrics));
98
99 data.delayedReply(data.error, data.response, responseBuffer);
100 data.delayedReply = nullptr;
101}
102
103NetworkResourceLoader::NetworkResourceLoader(NetworkResourceLoadParameters&& parameters, NetworkConnectionToWebProcess& connection, Messages::NetworkConnectionToWebProcess::PerformSynchronousLoad::DelayedReply&& synchronousReply)
104 : m_parameters { WTFMove(parameters) }
105 , m_connection { connection }
106 , m_fileReferences(connection.resolveBlobReferences(m_parameters))
107 , m_isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials { m_parameters.clientCredentialPolicy == ClientCredentialPolicy::MayAskClientForCredentials }
108 , m_bufferingTimer { *this, &NetworkResourceLoader::bufferingTimerFired }
109 , m_shouldCaptureExtraNetworkLoadMetrics(m_connection->captureExtraNetworkLoadMetricsEnabled())
110 , m_resourceLoadID { NetworkResourceLoadIdentifier::generate() }
111{
112 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
113
114 if (auto* session = connection.networkProcess().networkSession(sessionID()))
115 m_cache = session->cache();
116
117 // FIXME: This is necessary because of the existence of EmptyFrameLoaderClient in WebCore.
118 // Once bug 116233 is resolved, this ASSERT can just be "m_webPageID && m_webFrameID"
119 ASSERT((m_parameters.webPageID && m_parameters.webFrameID) || m_parameters.clientCredentialPolicy == ClientCredentialPolicy::CannotAskClientForCredentials);
120
121 if (synchronousReply || parameters.shouldRestrictHTTPResponseAccess || parameters.options.keepAlive) {
122 NetworkLoadChecker::LoadType requestLoadType = isMainFrameLoad() ? NetworkLoadChecker::LoadType::MainFrame : NetworkLoadChecker::LoadType::Other;
123 m_networkLoadChecker = makeUnique<NetworkLoadChecker>(connection.networkProcess(), this, &connection.schemeRegistry(), FetchOptions { m_parameters.options }, sessionID(), m_parameters.webPageProxyID, HTTPHeaderMap { m_parameters.originalRequestHeaders }, URL { m_parameters.request.url() }, URL { m_parameters.documentURL }, m_parameters.sourceOrigin.copyRef(), m_parameters.topOrigin.copyRef(), m_parameters.preflightPolicy, originalRequest().httpReferrer(), shouldCaptureExtraNetworkLoadMetrics(), requestLoadType);
124 if (m_parameters.cspResponseHeaders)
125 m_networkLoadChecker->setCSPResponseHeaders(ContentSecurityPolicyResponseHeaders { m_parameters.cspResponseHeaders.value() });
126#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
127 m_networkLoadChecker->setContentExtensionController(URL { m_parameters.mainDocumentURL }, m_parameters.userContentControllerIdentifier);
128#endif
129 }
130 if (synchronousReply)
131 m_synchronousLoadData = makeUnique<SynchronousLoadData>(WTFMove(synchronousReply));
132}
133
134NetworkResourceLoader::~NetworkResourceLoader()
135{
136 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
137 ASSERT(!m_networkLoad);
138 ASSERT(!isSynchronous() || !m_synchronousLoadData->delayedReply);
139 ASSERT(m_fileReferences.isEmpty());
140 if (m_responseCompletionHandler)
141 m_responseCompletionHandler(PolicyAction::Ignore);
142}
143
144bool NetworkResourceLoader::canUseCache(const ResourceRequest& request) const
145{
146 if (!m_cache)
147 return false;
148 ASSERT(!sessionID().isEphemeral());
149
150 if (!request.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
151 return false;
152 if (originalRequest().cachePolicy() == WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache)
153 return false;
154
155 return true;
156}
157
158bool NetworkResourceLoader::canUseCachedRedirect(const ResourceRequest& request) const
159{
160 if (!canUseCache(request) || m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation)
161 return false;
162 // Limit cached redirects to avoid cycles and other trouble.
163 // Networking layer follows over 30 redirects but caching that many seems unnecessary.
164 static const unsigned maximumCachedRedirectCount { 5 };
165 if (m_redirectCount > maximumCachedRedirectCount)
166 return false;
167
168 return true;
169}
170
171bool NetworkResourceLoader::isSynchronous() const
172{
173 return !!m_synchronousLoadData;
174}
175
176void NetworkResourceLoader::start()
177{
178 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
179 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("start: hasNetworkLoadChecker=%d", !!m_networkLoadChecker);
180
181 m_networkActivityTracker = m_connection->startTrackingResourceLoad(m_parameters.webPageID, m_parameters.identifier, isMainFrameLoad());
182
183 ASSERT(!m_wasStarted);
184 m_wasStarted = true;
185
186 if (m_networkLoadChecker) {
187 m_networkLoadChecker->check(ResourceRequest { originalRequest() }, this, [this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)] (auto&& result) {
188 if (!weakThis)
189 return;
190
191 WTF::switchOn(result,
192 [this] (ResourceError& error) {
193 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("start: NetworkLoadChecker::check returned an error (error.domain=%" PUBLIC_LOG_STRING ", error.code=%d, isCancellation=%d)", error.domain().utf8().data(), error.errorCode(), error.isCancellation());
194 if (!error.isCancellation())
195 this->didFailLoading(error);
196 },
197 [this] (NetworkLoadChecker::RedirectionTriplet& triplet) {
198 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("start: NetworkLoadChecker::check returned a synthetic redirect");
199 this->m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect = true;
200 this->willSendRedirectedRequest(WTFMove(triplet.request), WTFMove(triplet.redirectRequest), WTFMove(triplet.redirectResponse));
201 },
202 [this] (ResourceRequest& request) {
203 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("start: NetworkLoadChecker::check is done");
204 if (this->canUseCache(request)) {
205 this->retrieveCacheEntry(request);
206 return;
207 }
208
209 this->startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(request), FirstLoad::Yes);
210 }
211 );
212 });
213 return;
214 }
215 // FIXME: Remove that code path once m_networkLoadChecker is used for all network loads.
216 if (canUseCache(originalRequest())) {
217 retrieveCacheEntry(originalRequest());
218 return;
219 }
220
221 startNetworkLoad(ResourceRequest { originalRequest() }, FirstLoad::Yes);
222}
223
224void NetworkResourceLoader::retrieveCacheEntry(const ResourceRequest& request)
225{
226 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntry: isMainFrameLoad=%d", isMainFrameLoad());
227 ASSERT(canUseCache(request));
228
229 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
230 if (isMainFrameLoad()) {
231 ASSERT(m_parameters.options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Navigate);
232 if (auto* session = m_connection->networkProcess().networkSession(sessionID())) {
233 if (auto entry = session->prefetchCache().take(request.url())) {
234 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntry: retrieved an entry from the prefetch cache (isRedirect=%d)", !entry->redirectRequest.isNull());
235 if (!entry->redirectRequest.isNull()) {
236 auto cacheEntry = m_cache->makeRedirectEntry(request, entry->response, entry->redirectRequest);
237 retrieveCacheEntryInternal(WTFMove(cacheEntry), ResourceRequest { request });
238 auto maxAgeCap = validateCacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation(request, entry->redirectRequest, entry->response);
239 m_cache->storeRedirect(request, entry->response, entry->redirectRequest, maxAgeCap);
240 return;
241 }
242 auto buffer = entry->releaseBuffer();
243 auto cacheEntry = m_cache->makeEntry(request, entry->response, buffer.copyRef());
244 retrieveCacheEntryInternal(WTFMove(cacheEntry), ResourceRequest { request });
245 m_cache->store(request, entry->response, WTFMove(buffer));
246 return;
247 }
248 }
249 }
250
251 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntry: Checking the HTTP disk cache");
252 m_cache->retrieve(request, globalFrameID(), m_parameters.isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain, [this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), request = ResourceRequest { request }](auto entry, auto info) mutable {
253 if (!weakThis)
254 return;
255
256 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntry: Done checking the HTTP disk cache (foundCachedEntry=%d)", !!entry);
257 logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded(info);
258
259 if (!entry) {
260 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(request), FirstLoad::Yes);
261 return;
262 }
263 retrieveCacheEntryInternal(WTFMove(entry), WTFMove(request));
264 });
265}
266
267void NetworkResourceLoader::retrieveCacheEntryInternal(std::unique_ptr<NetworkCache::Entry>&& entry, WebCore::ResourceRequest&& request)
268{
269 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal:");
270#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
271 if (entry->hasReachedPrevalentResourceAgeCap()) {
272 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal: Revalidating cached entry because it reached the prevalent resource age cap");
273 m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation = WTFMove(entry);
274 ResourceRequest revalidationRequest = originalRequest();
275 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(revalidationRequest), FirstLoad::Yes);
276 return;
277 }
278#endif
279 if (entry->redirectRequest()) {
280 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal: Cached entry is a redirect");
281 dispatchWillSendRequestForCacheEntry(WTFMove(request), WTFMove(entry));
282 return;
283 }
284 if (m_parameters.needsCertificateInfo && !entry->response().certificateInfo()) {
285 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal: Cached entry is missing certificate information so we are not using it");
286 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(request), FirstLoad::Yes);
287 return;
288 }
289 if (entry->needsValidation() || request.cachePolicy() == WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData) {
290 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal: Cached entry needs revalidation");
291 validateCacheEntry(WTFMove(entry));
292 return;
293 }
294 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("retrieveCacheEntryInternal: Cached entry is directly usable");
295 didRetrieveCacheEntry(WTFMove(entry));
296}
297
298void NetworkResourceLoader::startNetworkLoad(ResourceRequest&& request, FirstLoad load)
299{
300 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startNetworkLoad: (isFirstLoad=%d, timeout=%f)", load == FirstLoad::Yes, request.timeoutInterval());
301 if (load == FirstLoad::Yes) {
302 consumeSandboxExtensions();
303
304 if (isSynchronous() || m_parameters.maximumBufferingTime > 0_s)
305 m_bufferedData = SharedBuffer::create();
306
307 if (canUseCache(request))
308 m_bufferedDataForCache = SharedBuffer::create();
309 }
310
311 NetworkLoadParameters parameters = m_parameters;
312 parameters.networkActivityTracker = m_networkActivityTracker;
313 if (parameters.storedCredentialsPolicy == WebCore::StoredCredentialsPolicy::Use && m_networkLoadChecker)
314 parameters.storedCredentialsPolicy = m_networkLoadChecker->storedCredentialsPolicy();
315
316 auto* networkSession = m_connection->networkSession();
317 if (!networkSession) {
318 WTFLogAlways("Attempted to create a NetworkLoad with a session (id=%" PRIu64 ") that does not exist.", sessionID().toUInt64());
319 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("startNetworkLoad: Attempted to create a NetworkLoad for a session that does not exist (sessionID=%" PRIu64 ")", sessionID().toUInt64());
320 m_connection->networkProcess().logDiagnosticMessage(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, WebCore::DiagnosticLoggingKeys::internalErrorKey(), WebCore::DiagnosticLoggingKeys::invalidSessionIDKey(), WebCore::ShouldSample::No);
321 didFailLoading(internalError(request.url()));
322 return;
323 }
324
325 if (request.url().protocolIsBlob())
326 parameters.blobFileReferences = networkSession->blobRegistry().filesInBlob(originalRequest().url());
327
328 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient) {
329 std::optional<IPC::FormDataReference> httpBody;
330 if (auto* formData = request.httpBody()) {
331 static constexpr auto maxSerializedRequestSize = 1024 * 1024;
332 if (formData->lengthInBytes() <= maxSerializedRequestSize)
333 httpBody = IPC::FormDataReference { formData };
334 }
335 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidSendRequest(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), request, httpBody), 0);
336 }
337
338 parameters.request = WTFMove(request);
339 parameters.isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain = m_parameters.isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain;
340 m_networkLoad = makeUnique<NetworkLoad>(*this, &networkSession->blobRegistry(), WTFMove(parameters), *networkSession);
341
342 if (isSynchronous())
343 m_networkLoad->start();
344 else
345 m_networkLoad->startWithScheduling();
346
347 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startNetworkLoad: Going to the network (description=%" PUBLIC_LOG_STRING ")", m_networkLoad->description().utf8().data());
348}
349
350ResourceLoadInfo NetworkResourceLoader::resourceLoadInfo()
351{
352 auto loadedFromCache = [] (const ResourceResponse& response) {
353 switch (response.source()) {
354 case ResourceResponse::Source::DiskCache:
355 case ResourceResponse::Source::DiskCacheAfterValidation:
356 case ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCache:
357 case ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCacheAfterValidation:
358 case ResourceResponse::Source::ApplicationCache:
359 case ResourceResponse::Source::DOMCache:
360 return true;
361 case ResourceResponse::Source::Unknown:
362 case ResourceResponse::Source::Network:
363 case ResourceResponse::Source::ServiceWorker:
364 case ResourceResponse::Source::InspectorOverride:
365 break;
366 }
367 return false;
368 };
369
370 auto resourceType = [] (WebCore::ResourceRequestBase::Requester requester, WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination destination) {
371 switch (requester) {
372 case WebCore::ResourceRequestBase::Requester::XHR:
373 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::XMLHTTPRequest;
374 case WebCore::ResourceRequestBase::Requester::Fetch:
375 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Fetch;
376 case WebCore::ResourceRequestBase::Requester::Ping:
377 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Ping;
378 case WebCore::ResourceRequestBase::Requester::Beacon:
379 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Beacon;
380 default:
381 break;
382 }
383
384 switch (destination) {
385 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::EmptyString:
386 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
387 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Audio:
388 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Media;
389 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Audioworklet:
390 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
391 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Document:
392 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Document;
393 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Embed:
394 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Object;
395 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Font:
396 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Font;
397 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Image:
398 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Image;
399 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Manifest:
400 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::ApplicationManifest;
401 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Model:
402 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Media;
403 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Object:
404 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Object;
405 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Paintworklet:
406 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
407 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Report:
408 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::CSPReport;
409 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Script:
410 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Script;
411 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Serviceworker:
412 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
413 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Sharedworker:
414 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
415 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Style:
416 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Stylesheet;
417 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Track:
418 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Media;
419 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Video:
420 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Media;
421 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Worker:
422 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
423 case WebCore::FetchOptions::Destination::Xslt:
424 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::XSLT;
425 }
426
427 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
428 return ResourceLoadInfo::Type::Other;
429 };
430
431 return ResourceLoadInfo {
432 m_resourceLoadID,
433 m_parameters.webFrameID,
434 m_parameters.parentFrameID,
435 originalRequest().url(),
436 originalRequest().httpMethod(),
437 WallTime::now(),
438 loadedFromCache(m_response),
439 resourceType(originalRequest().requester(), m_parameters.options.destination)
440 };
441}
442
443void NetworkResourceLoader::cleanup(LoadResult result)
444{
445 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
446 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("cleanup: (result=%u)", static_cast<unsigned>(result));
447
448 NetworkActivityTracker::CompletionCode code { };
449 switch (result) {
450 case LoadResult::Unknown:
451 code = NetworkActivityTracker::CompletionCode::Undefined;
452 break;
453 case LoadResult::Success:
454 code = NetworkActivityTracker::CompletionCode::Success;
455 break;
456 case LoadResult::Failure:
457 code = NetworkActivityTracker::CompletionCode::Failure;
458 break;
459 case LoadResult::Cancel:
460 code = NetworkActivityTracker::CompletionCode::Cancel;
461 break;
462 }
463
464 m_connection->stopTrackingResourceLoad(m_parameters.identifier, code);
465
466 m_bufferingTimer.stop();
467
468 invalidateSandboxExtensions();
469
470 m_networkLoad = nullptr;
471
472 // This will cause NetworkResourceLoader to be destroyed and therefore we do it last.
473 m_connection->didCleanupResourceLoader(*this);
474}
475
476void NetworkResourceLoader::convertToDownload(DownloadID downloadID, const ResourceRequest& request, const ResourceResponse& response)
477{
478 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("convertToDownload: (downloadID=%" PRIu64 ", hasNetworkLoad=%d, hasResponseCompletionHandler=%d)", downloadID.toUInt64(), !!m_networkLoad, !!m_responseCompletionHandler);
479
480 // This can happen if the resource came from the disk cache.
481 if (!m_networkLoad) {
482 m_connection->networkProcess().downloadManager().startDownload(sessionID(), downloadID, request, m_parameters.isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain);
483 abort();
484 return;
485 }
486
487 if (m_responseCompletionHandler)
488 m_connection->networkProcess().downloadManager().convertNetworkLoadToDownload(downloadID, std::exchange(m_networkLoad, nullptr), WTFMove(m_responseCompletionHandler), WTFMove(m_fileReferences), request, response);
489}
490
491void NetworkResourceLoader::abort()
492{
493 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("abort: (hasNetworkLoad=%d)", !!m_networkLoad);
494 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
495
496 if (m_parameters.options.keepAlive && m_response.isNull() && !m_isKeptAlive) {
497 m_isKeptAlive = true;
498 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("abort: Keeping network load alive due to keepalive option");
499 m_connection->transferKeptAliveLoad(*this);
500 return;
501 }
502
503#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
504 if (auto task = WTFMove(m_serviceWorkerFetchTask)) {
505 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("abort: Cancelling pending service worker fetch task (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", task->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64());
506 task->cancelFromClient();
507 }
508#endif
509
510 if (m_networkLoad) {
511 if (canUseCache(m_networkLoad->currentRequest())) {
512 // We might already have used data from this incomplete load. Ensure older versions don't remain in the cache after cancel.
513 if (!m_response.isNull())
514 m_cache->remove(m_networkLoad->currentRequest());
515 }
516 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("abort: Cancelling network load");
517 m_networkLoad->cancel();
518 }
519
520 cleanup(LoadResult::Cancel);
521}
522
523bool NetworkResourceLoader::shouldInterruptLoadForXFrameOptions(const String& xFrameOptions, const URL& url)
524{
525 if (isMainFrameLoad())
526 return false;
527
528 switch (parseXFrameOptionsHeader(xFrameOptions)) {
529 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::None:
530 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::AllowAll:
531 return false;
532 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Deny:
533 return true;
534 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::SameOrigin: {
535 auto origin = SecurityOrigin::create(url);
536 auto topFrameOrigin = m_parameters.frameAncestorOrigins.last();
537 if (!origin->isSameSchemeHostPort(*topFrameOrigin))
538 return true;
539 for (auto& ancestorOrigin : m_parameters.frameAncestorOrigins) {
540 if (!origin->isSameSchemeHostPort(*ancestorOrigin))
541 return true;
542 }
543 return false;
544 }
545 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Conflict: {
546 String errorMessage = "Multiple 'X-Frame-Options' headers with conflicting values ('" + xFrameOptions + "') encountered when loading '" + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "'. Falling back to 'DENY'.";
547 send(Messages::WebPage::AddConsoleMessage { m_parameters.webFrameID, MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, errorMessage, identifier() }, m_parameters.webPageID);
548 return true;
549 }
550 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Invalid: {
551 String errorMessage = "Invalid 'X-Frame-Options' header encountered when loading '" + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "': '" + xFrameOptions + "' is not a recognized directive. The header will be ignored.";
552 send(Messages::WebPage::AddConsoleMessage { m_parameters.webFrameID, MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, errorMessage, identifier() }, m_parameters.webPageID);
553 return false;
554 }
555 }
556 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
557 return false;
558}
559
560bool NetworkResourceLoader::shouldInterruptLoadForCSPFrameAncestorsOrXFrameOptions(const ResourceResponse& response)
561{
562 ASSERT(isMainResource());
563
564#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
565 if (PreviewConverter::supportsMIMEType(response.mimeType()))
566 return false;
567#endif
568
569 auto url = response.url();
570 ContentSecurityPolicy contentSecurityPolicy { URL { url }, this };
571 contentSecurityPolicy.didReceiveHeaders(ContentSecurityPolicyResponseHeaders { response }, originalRequest().httpReferrer());
572 if (!contentSecurityPolicy.allowFrameAncestors(m_parameters.frameAncestorOrigins, url))
573 return true;
574
575 if (!contentSecurityPolicy.overridesXFrameOptions()) {
576 String xFrameOptions = m_response.httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::XFrameOptions);
577 if (!xFrameOptions.isNull() && shouldInterruptLoadForXFrameOptions(xFrameOptions, response.url())) {
578 String errorMessage = "Refused to display '" + response.url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "' in a frame because it set 'X-Frame-Options' to '" + xFrameOptions + "'.";
579 send(Messages::WebPage::AddConsoleMessage { m_parameters.webFrameID, MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, errorMessage, identifier() }, m_parameters.webPageID);
580 return true;
581 }
582 }
583 return false;
584}
585
586void NetworkResourceLoader::didReceiveResponse(ResourceResponse&& receivedResponse, ResponseCompletionHandler&& completionHandler)
587{
588 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: (httpStatusCode=%d, MIMEType=%" PUBLIC_LOG_STRING ", expectedContentLength=%" PRId64 ", hasCachedEntryForValidation=%d, hasNetworkLoadChecker=%d)", receivedResponse.httpStatusCode(), receivedResponse.mimeType().utf8().data(), receivedResponse.expectedContentLength(), !!m_cacheEntryForValidation, !!m_networkLoadChecker);
589
590 if (isMainResource())
591 didReceiveMainResourceResponse(receivedResponse);
592
593 m_response = WTFMove(receivedResponse);
594
595 if (shouldCaptureExtraNetworkLoadMetrics() && m_networkLoadChecker) {
596 auto information = m_networkLoadChecker->takeNetworkLoadInformation();
597 information.response = m_response;
598 m_connection->addNetworkLoadInformation(identifier(), WTFMove(information));
599 }
600
601 // For multipart/x-mixed-replace didReceiveResponseAsync gets called multiple times and buffering would require special handling.
602 if (!isSynchronous() && m_response.isMultipart())
603 m_bufferedData = nullptr;
604
605 if (m_response.isMultipart())
606 m_bufferedDataForCache = nullptr;
607
608 if (m_cacheEntryForValidation) {
609 bool validationSucceeded = m_response.httpStatusCode() == 304; // 304 Not Modified
610 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Received revalidation response (validationSucceeded=%d, wasOriginalRequestConditional=%d)", validationSucceeded, originalRequest().isConditional());
611 if (validationSucceeded) {
612 m_cacheEntryForValidation = m_cache->update(originalRequest(), *m_cacheEntryForValidation, m_response);
613 // If the request was conditional then this revalidation was not triggered by the network cache and we pass the 304 response to WebCore.
614 if (originalRequest().isConditional())
615 m_cacheEntryForValidation = nullptr;
616 } else
617 m_cacheEntryForValidation = nullptr;
618 }
619 if (m_cacheEntryForValidation)
620 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Use);
621
622 if (isMainResource() && shouldInterruptLoadForCSPFrameAncestorsOrXFrameOptions(m_response)) {
623 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("didReceiveResponse: Interrupting main resource load due to CSP frame-ancestors or X-Frame-Options");
624 auto response = sanitizeResponseIfPossible(ResourceResponse { m_response }, ResourceResponse::SanitizationType::CrossOriginSafe);
625 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::StopLoadingAfterXFrameOptionsOrContentSecurityPolicyDenied { response });
626 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Ignore);
627 }
628
629 if (m_networkLoadChecker) {
630 auto error = m_networkLoadChecker->validateResponse(m_networkLoad ? m_networkLoad->currentRequest() : originalRequest(), m_response);
631 if (!error.isNull()) {
632 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("didReceiveResponse: NetworkLoadChecker::validateResponse returned an error (error.domain=%" PUBLIC_LOG_STRING ", error.code=%d)", error.domain().utf8().data(), error.errorCode());
633 RunLoop::main().dispatch([protectedThis = makeRef(*this), error = WTFMove(error)] {
634 if (protectedThis->m_networkLoad)
635 protectedThis->didFailLoading(error);
636 });
637 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Ignore);
638 }
639 }
640
641 auto response = sanitizeResponseIfPossible(ResourceResponse { m_response }, ResourceResponse::SanitizationType::CrossOriginSafe);
642 if (isSynchronous()) {
643 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Using response for synchronous load");
644 m_synchronousLoadData->response = WTFMove(response);
645 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Use);
646 }
647
648 if (isCrossOriginPrefetch()) {
649 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Using response for cross-origin prefetch");
650 if (response.httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Vary).contains("Cookie")) {
651 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Canceling cross-origin prefetch for Vary: Cookie");
652 abort();
653 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Ignore);
654 }
655 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Use);
656 }
657
658 // We wait to receive message NetworkResourceLoader::ContinueDidReceiveResponse before continuing a load for
659 // a main resource because the embedding client must decide whether to allow the load.
660 bool willWaitForContinueDidReceiveResponse = isMainResource();
661 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Sending WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse IPC (willWaitForContinueDidReceiveResponse=%d)", willWaitForContinueDidReceiveResponse);
662 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse { response, willWaitForContinueDidReceiveResponse });
663
664 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient)
665 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidReceiveResponse(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), response), 0);
666
667 if (willWaitForContinueDidReceiveResponse) {
668 m_responseCompletionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler);
669 return;
670 }
671
672 if (m_isKeptAlive) {
673 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Ignoring response because of keepalive option");
674 return completionHandler(PolicyAction::Ignore);
675 }
676
677 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveResponse: Using response");
678 completionHandler(PolicyAction::Use);
679}
680
681void NetworkResourceLoader::didReceiveBuffer(Ref<SharedBuffer>&& buffer, int reportedEncodedDataLength)
682{
683 if (!m_numBytesReceived)
684 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveBuffer: Started receiving data (reportedEncodedDataLength=%d)", reportedEncodedDataLength);
685 m_numBytesReceived += buffer->size();
686
687 ASSERT(!m_cacheEntryForValidation);
688
689 if (m_bufferedDataForCache) {
690 // Prevent memory growth in case of streaming data and limit size of entries in the cache.
691 const size_t maximumCacheBufferSize = m_cache->capacity() / 8;
692 if (m_bufferedDataForCache->size() + buffer->size() <= maximumCacheBufferSize)
693 m_bufferedDataForCache->append(buffer.get());
694 else
695 m_bufferedDataForCache = nullptr;
696 }
697 if (isCrossOriginPrefetch())
698 return;
699 // FIXME: At least on OS X Yosemite we always get -1 from the resource handle.
700 unsigned encodedDataLength = reportedEncodedDataLength >= 0 ? reportedEncodedDataLength : buffer->size();
701
702 if (m_bufferedData) {
703 m_bufferedData->append(buffer.get());
704 m_bufferedDataEncodedDataLength += encodedDataLength;
705 startBufferingTimerIfNeeded();
706 return;
707 }
708 sendBuffer(buffer, encodedDataLength);
709}
710
711void NetworkResourceLoader::didFinishLoading(const NetworkLoadMetrics& networkLoadMetrics)
712{
713 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didFinishLoading: (numBytesReceived=%zd, hasCacheEntryForValidation=%d)", m_numBytesReceived, !!m_cacheEntryForValidation);
714
715 if (shouldCaptureExtraNetworkLoadMetrics())
716 m_connection->addNetworkLoadInformationMetrics(identifier(), networkLoadMetrics);
717
718 if (m_cacheEntryForValidation) {
719 // 304 Not Modified
720 ASSERT(m_response.httpStatusCode() == 304);
721 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) revalidated");
722 didRetrieveCacheEntry(WTFMove(m_cacheEntryForValidation));
723 return;
724 }
725
726#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS) && !RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
727 if (shouldLogCookieInformation(m_connection, sessionID()))
728 logCookieInformation();
729#endif
730
731 if (isSynchronous())
732 sendReplyToSynchronousRequest(*m_synchronousLoadData, m_bufferedData.get(), networkLoadMetrics);
733 else {
734 if (m_bufferedData && !m_bufferedData->isEmpty()) {
735 // FIXME: Pass a real value or remove the encoded data size feature.
736 sendBuffer(*m_bufferedData, -1);
737 }
738 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFinishResourceLoad(networkLoadMetrics));
739 }
740
741 tryStoreAsCacheEntry();
742
743 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient)
744 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidCompleteWithError(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), m_response, { }), 0);
745
746 cleanup(LoadResult::Success);
747}
748
749void NetworkResourceLoader::didFailLoading(const ResourceError& error)
750{
751 bool wasServiceWorkerLoad = false;
752#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
753 wasServiceWorkerLoad = !!m_serviceWorkerFetchTask;
754#endif
755 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("didFailLoading: (wasServiceWorkerLoad=%d, isTimeout=%d, isCancellation=%d, isAccessControl=%d, errorCode=%d)", wasServiceWorkerLoad, error.isTimeout(), error.isCancellation(), error.isAccessControl(), error.errorCode());
756 UNUSED_VARIABLE(wasServiceWorkerLoad);
757
758 if (shouldCaptureExtraNetworkLoadMetrics())
759 m_connection->removeNetworkLoadInformation(identifier());
760
761 ASSERT(!error.isNull());
762
763 m_cacheEntryForValidation = nullptr;
764
765 if (isSynchronous()) {
766 m_synchronousLoadData->error = error;
767 sendReplyToSynchronousRequest(*m_synchronousLoadData, nullptr, { });
768 } else if (auto* connection = messageSenderConnection()) {
769#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
770 if (m_serviceWorkerFetchTask)
771 connection->send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFailServiceWorkerLoad(error), messageSenderDestinationID());
772 else
773 connection->send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFailResourceLoad(error), messageSenderDestinationID());
774#else
775 connection->send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFailResourceLoad(error), messageSenderDestinationID());
776#endif
777 }
778
779 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient)
780 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidCompleteWithError(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), { }, error), 0);
781
782 cleanup(LoadResult::Failure);
783}
784
785void NetworkResourceLoader::didBlockAuthenticationChallenge()
786{
787 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didBlockAuthenticationChallenge:");
788 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidBlockAuthenticationChallenge());
789}
790
791void NetworkResourceLoader::didReceiveChallenge(const AuthenticationChallenge& challenge)
792{
793 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient)
794 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidReceiveChallenge(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), challenge), 0);
795}
796
797std::optional<Seconds> NetworkResourceLoader::validateCacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation(const ResourceRequest& request, const ResourceRequest& redirectRequest, const ResourceResponse& redirectResponse)
798{
799#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
800 bool existingCacheEntryMatchesNewResponse = false;
801 if (m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation) {
802 ASSERT(redirectResponse.source() == ResourceResponse::Source::Network);
803 ASSERT(redirectResponse.isRedirection());
804 if (redirectResponse.httpHeaderField(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Location) == m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation->response().httpHeaderField(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Location))
805 existingCacheEntryMatchesNewResponse = true;
806
807 m_cache->remove(m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation->key());
808 m_cacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation = nullptr;
809 }
810
811 if (!existingCacheEntryMatchesNewResponse) {
812 if (auto* networkStorageSession = m_connection->networkProcess().storageSession(sessionID()))
813 return networkStorageSession->maxAgeCacheCap(request);
814 }
815#endif
816 return std::nullopt;
817}
818
819void NetworkResourceLoader::willSendRedirectedRequest(ResourceRequest&& request, ResourceRequest&& redirectRequest, ResourceResponse&& redirectResponse)
820{
821 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRedirectedRequest:");
822 ++m_redirectCount;
823 m_redirectResponse = redirectResponse;
824
825 std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement::AttributionTriggerData> privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData;
826 if (!sessionID().isEphemeral()) {
827 if (auto result = PrivateClickMeasurement::parseAttributionRequest(redirectRequest.url()))
828 privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData = result.value();
829 else if (!result.error().isEmpty())
830 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::PrivateClickMeasurement, MessageLevel::Error, result.error());
831 }
832
833 auto maxAgeCap = validateCacheEntryForMaxAgeCapValidation(request, redirectRequest, redirectResponse);
834 if (redirectResponse.source() == ResourceResponse::Source::Network && canUseCachedRedirect(request))
835 m_cache->storeRedirect(request, redirectResponse, redirectRequest, maxAgeCap);
836
837 if (m_networkLoadChecker) {
838 if (privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData)
839 m_networkLoadChecker->enableContentExtensionsCheck();
840 m_networkLoadChecker->storeRedirectionIfNeeded(request, redirectResponse);
841
842 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRedirectedRequest: Checking redirect using NetworkLoadChecker");
843 m_networkLoadChecker->checkRedirection(WTFMove(request), WTFMove(redirectRequest), WTFMove(redirectResponse), this, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this, storedCredentialsPolicy = m_networkLoadChecker->storedCredentialsPolicy(), privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData = WTFMove(privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData)](auto&& result) mutable {
844 if (!result.has_value()) {
845 if (result.error().isCancellation()) {
846 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRedirectedRequest: NetworkLoadChecker::checkRedirection returned with a cancellation");
847 return;
848 }
849
850 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("willSendRedirectedRequest: NetworkLoadChecker::checkRedirection returned an error");
851 this->didFailLoading(result.error());
852 return;
853 }
854
855 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRedirectedRequest: NetworkLoadChecker::checkRedirection is done");
856 if (m_parameters.options.redirect == FetchOptions::Redirect::Manual) {
857 this->didFinishWithRedirectResponse(WTFMove(result->request), WTFMove(result->redirectRequest), WTFMove(result->redirectResponse));
858 return;
859 }
860
861 if (this->isSynchronous()) {
862 if (storedCredentialsPolicy != m_networkLoadChecker->storedCredentialsPolicy()) {
863 // We need to restart the load to update the session according the new credential policy.
864 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("willSendRedirectedRequest: Restarting network load due to credential policy change for synchronous load");
865 this->restartNetworkLoad(WTFMove(result->redirectRequest));
866 return;
867 }
868
869 // We do not support prompting for credentials for synchronous loads. If we ever change this policy then
870 // we need to take care to prompt if and only if request and redirectRequest are not mixed content.
871 this->continueWillSendRequest(WTFMove(result->redirectRequest), false);
872 return;
873 }
874
875 m_shouldRestartLoad = storedCredentialsPolicy != m_networkLoadChecker->storedCredentialsPolicy();
876 this->continueWillSendRedirectedRequest(WTFMove(result->request), WTFMove(result->redirectRequest), WTFMove(result->redirectResponse), WTFMove(privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData));
877 });
878 return;
879 }
880 continueWillSendRedirectedRequest(WTFMove(request), WTFMove(redirectRequest), WTFMove(redirectResponse), WTFMove(privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData));
881}
882
883void NetworkResourceLoader::continueWillSendRedirectedRequest(ResourceRequest&& request, ResourceRequest&& redirectRequest, ResourceResponse&& redirectResponse, std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement::AttributionTriggerData>&& privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData)
884{
885 redirectRequest.setIsAppBound(request.isAppBound());
886
887 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRedirectedRequest: (m_isKeptAlive=%d, hasAdClickConversion=%d)", m_isKeptAlive, !!privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData);
888 ASSERT(!isSynchronous());
889
890 NetworkSession* networkSession = nullptr;
891 if (privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData && (networkSession = m_connection->networkProcess().networkSession(sessionID())))
892 networkSession->handlePrivateClickMeasurementConversion(WTFMove(*privateClickMeasurementAttributionTriggerData), request.url(), redirectRequest);
893
894 if (m_isKeptAlive) {
895 continueWillSendRequest(WTFMove(redirectRequest), false);
896 return;
897 }
898
899 // We send the request body separately because the ResourceRequest body normally does not get encoded when sent over IPC, as an optimization.
900 // However, we really need the body here because a redirect cross-site may cause a process-swap and the request to start again in a new WebContent process.
901 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::WillSendRequest(redirectRequest, IPC::FormDataReference { redirectRequest.httpBody() }, sanitizeResponseIfPossible(WTFMove(redirectResponse), ResourceResponse::SanitizationType::Redirection)));
902}
903
904void NetworkResourceLoader::didFinishWithRedirectResponse(WebCore::ResourceRequest&& request, WebCore::ResourceRequest&& redirectRequest, ResourceResponse&& redirectResponse)
905{
906 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didFinishWithRedirectResponse:");
907 redirectResponse.setType(ResourceResponse::Type::Opaqueredirect);
908 if (!isCrossOriginPrefetch())
909 didReceiveResponse(WTFMove(redirectResponse), [] (auto) { });
910 else if (auto* session = m_connection->networkProcess().networkSession(sessionID()))
911 session->prefetchCache().storeRedirect(request.url(), WTFMove(redirectResponse), WTFMove(redirectRequest));
912
913 WebCore::NetworkLoadMetrics networkLoadMetrics;
914 networkLoadMetrics.markComplete();
915 networkLoadMetrics.responseBodyBytesReceived = 0;
916 networkLoadMetrics.responseBodyDecodedSize = 0;
917 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFinishResourceLoad { networkLoadMetrics });
918
919 cleanup(LoadResult::Success);
920}
921
922static bool shouldSanitizeResponse(const NetworkProcess& process, std::optional<PageIdentifier> pageIdentifier, const FetchOptions& options, const URL& url)
923{
924 if (!pageIdentifier || options.destination != FetchOptions::Destination::EmptyString || options.mode != FetchOptions::Mode::NoCors)
925 return true;
926 return !process.shouldDisableCORSForRequestTo(*pageIdentifier, url);
927}
928
929ResourceResponse NetworkResourceLoader::sanitizeResponseIfPossible(ResourceResponse&& response, ResourceResponse::SanitizationType type)
930{
931 if (!m_parameters.shouldRestrictHTTPResponseAccess)
932 return WTFMove(response);
933
934 if (shouldSanitizeResponse(m_connection->networkProcess(), pageID(), parameters().options, originalRequest().url()))
935 response.sanitizeHTTPHeaderFields(type);
936
937 return WTFMove(response);
938}
939
940void NetworkResourceLoader::restartNetworkLoad(WebCore::ResourceRequest&& newRequest)
941{
942 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("restartNetworkLoad: (hasNetworkLoad=%d)", !!m_networkLoad);
943
944 if (m_networkLoad) {
945 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("restartNetworkLoad: Cancelling existing network load so we can restart the load.");
946 m_networkLoad->cancel();
947 }
948
949 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(newRequest), FirstLoad::No);
950}
951
952void NetworkResourceLoader::continueWillSendRequest(ResourceRequest&& newRequest, bool isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials)
953{
954 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: (isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials=%d)", isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials);
955
956#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
957 if (parameters().options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Navigate) {
958 if (auto serviceWorkerFetchTask = m_connection->createFetchTask(*this, newRequest)) {
959 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: Created a ServiceWorkerFetchTask to handle the redirect (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", serviceWorkerFetchTask->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64());
960 m_networkLoad = nullptr;
961 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask = WTFMove(serviceWorkerFetchTask);
962 return;
963 }
964 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: Navigation is not using service workers");
965 m_shouldRestartLoad = !!m_serviceWorkerFetchTask;
966 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask = nullptr;
967 }
968 if (m_serviceWorkerFetchTask) {
969 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: Continuing fetch task with redirect (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64());
970 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->continueFetchTaskWith(WTFMove(newRequest));
971 return;
972 }
973#endif
974
975 if (m_shouldRestartLoad) {
976 m_shouldRestartLoad = false;
977
978 if (m_networkLoad)
979 m_networkLoad->updateRequestAfterRedirection(newRequest);
980
981 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: Restarting network load");
982 restartNetworkLoad(WTFMove(newRequest));
983 return;
984 }
985
986 if (m_networkLoadChecker) {
987 // FIXME: We should be doing this check when receiving the redirection and not allow about protocol as per fetch spec.
988 if (!newRequest.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !newRequest.url().protocolIsAbout() && m_redirectCount) {
989 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("continueWillSendRequest: Failing load because it redirected to a scheme that is not HTTP(S)");
990 didFailLoading(ResourceError { String { }, 0, newRequest.url(), "Redirection to URL with a scheme that is not HTTP(S)"_s, ResourceError::Type::AccessControl });
991 return;
992 }
993 }
994
995 m_isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials = isAllowedToAskUserForCredentials;
996
997 // If there is a match in the network cache, we need to reuse the original cache policy and partition.
998 newRequest.setCachePolicy(originalRequest().cachePolicy());
999 newRequest.setCachePartition(originalRequest().cachePartition());
1000
1001 if (m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect) {
1002 m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect = false;
1003
1004 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) Retrieving cached redirect");
1005 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect was set");
1006
1007 if (canUseCachedRedirect(newRequest))
1008 retrieveCacheEntry(newRequest);
1009 else
1010 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(newRequest), FirstLoad::Yes);
1011
1012 return;
1013 }
1014
1015 if (m_networkLoad) {
1016 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueWillSendRequest: Telling NetworkLoad to proceed with the redirect");
1017
1018 if (m_parameters.pageHasResourceLoadClient && !newRequest.isNull())
1019 m_connection->networkProcess().parentProcessConnection()->send(Messages::NetworkProcessProxy::ResourceLoadDidPerformHTTPRedirection(m_parameters.webPageProxyID, resourceLoadInfo(), m_redirectResponse, newRequest), 0);
1020
1021 m_networkLoad->continueWillSendRequest(WTFMove(newRequest));
1022 }
1023}
1024
1025void NetworkResourceLoader::continueDidReceiveResponse()
1026{
1027 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueDidReceiveResponse: (hasCacheEntryWaitingForContinueDidReceiveResponse=%d, hasResponseCompletionHandler=%d)", !!m_cacheEntryWaitingForContinueDidReceiveResponse, !!m_responseCompletionHandler);
1028#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1029 if (m_serviceWorkerFetchTask) {
1030 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("continueDidReceiveResponse: continuing with ServiceWorkerFetchTask (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64());
1031 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->continueDidReceiveFetchResponse();
1032 return;
1033 }
1034#endif
1035
1036 if (m_cacheEntryWaitingForContinueDidReceiveResponse) {
1037 sendResultForCacheEntry(WTFMove(m_cacheEntryWaitingForContinueDidReceiveResponse));
1038 cleanup(LoadResult::Success);
1039 return;
1040 }
1041
1042 if (m_responseCompletionHandler)
1043 m_responseCompletionHandler(PolicyAction::Use);
1044}

1047{
1048 if (!isSynchronous())
1049 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidSendData(bytesSent, totalBytesToBeSent));
1050}

1052void NetworkResourceLoader::startBufferingTimerIfNeeded()
1053{
1054 if (isSynchronous())
1055 return;
1056 if (m_bufferingTimer.isActive())
1057 return;
1058 m_bufferingTimer.startOneShot(m_parameters.maximumBufferingTime);
1059}
1060
1061void NetworkResourceLoader::bufferingTimerFired()
1062{
1063 ASSERT(m_bufferedData);
1064 ASSERT(m_networkLoad);
1065
1066 if (m_bufferedData->isEmpty())
1067 return;
1068
1069 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveData({ *m_bufferedData }, m_bufferedDataEncodedDataLength));
1070
1071 m_bufferedData = SharedBuffer::create();
1072 m_bufferedDataEncodedDataLength = 0;
1073}

1075void NetworkResourceLoader::sendBuffer(SharedBuffer& buffer, size_t encodedDataLength)
1076{
1077 ASSERT(!isSynchronous());
1078
1079 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveData({ buffer }, encodedDataLength));
1080}
1081
1082void NetworkResourceLoader::tryStoreAsCacheEntry()
1083{
1084 if (!canUseCache(m_networkLoad->currentRequest())) {
1085 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("tryStoreAsCacheEntry: Not storing cache entry because request is not eligible");
1086 return;
1087 }
1088 if (!m_bufferedDataForCache) {
1089 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("tryStoreAsCacheEntry: Not storing cache entry because m_bufferedDataForCache is null");
1090 return;
1091 }
1092
1093 if (isCrossOriginPrefetch()) {
1094 if (auto* session = m_connection->networkProcess().networkSession(sessionID())) {
1095 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("tryStoreAsCacheEntry: Storing entry in prefetch cache");
1096 session->prefetchCache().store(m_networkLoad->currentRequest().url(), WTFMove(m_response), WTFMove(m_bufferedDataForCache));
1097 }
1098 return;
1099 }
1100 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("tryStoreAsCacheEntry: Storing entry in HTTP disk cache");
1101 m_cache->store(m_networkLoad->currentRequest(), m_response, WTFMove(m_bufferedDataForCache), [loader = makeRef(*this)](auto& mappedBody) mutable {
1102#if ENABLE(SHAREABLE_RESOURCE)
1103 if (mappedBody.shareableResourceHandle.isNull())
1104 return;
1105 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) sending DidCacheResource");
1106 loader->send(Messages::NetworkProcessConnection::DidCacheResource(loader->originalRequest(), mappedBody.shareableResourceHandle));
1107#endif
1108 });
1109}
1110
1111void NetworkResourceLoader::didReceiveMainResourceResponse(const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response)
1112{
1113 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didReceiveMainResourceResponse:");
1114#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
1115 if (auto* speculativeLoadManager = m_cache ? m_cache->speculativeLoadManager() : nullptr)
1116 speculativeLoadManager->registerMainResourceLoadResponse(globalFrameID(), originalRequest(), response);
1117#endif
1118}
1119
1120void NetworkResourceLoader::didRetrieveCacheEntry(std::unique_ptr<NetworkCache::Entry> entry)
1121{
1122 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didRetrieveCacheEntry:");
1123 auto response = entry->response();
1124
1125 if (isMainResource())
1126 didReceiveMainResourceResponse(response);
1127
1128 if (isMainResource() && shouldInterruptLoadForCSPFrameAncestorsOrXFrameOptions(response)) {
1129 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("didRetrieveCacheEntry: Stopping load due to CSP Frame-Ancestors or X-Frame-Options");
1130 response = sanitizeResponseIfPossible(WTFMove(response), ResourceResponse::SanitizationType::CrossOriginSafe);
1131 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::StopLoadingAfterXFrameOptionsOrContentSecurityPolicyDenied { response });
1132 return;
1133 }
1134 if (m_networkLoadChecker) {
1135 auto error = m_networkLoadChecker->validateResponse(originalRequest(), response);
1136 if (!error.isNull()) {
1137 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("didRetrieveCacheEntry: Failing load due to NetworkLoadChecker::validateResponse");
1138 didFailLoading(error);
1139 return;
1140 }
1141 }
1142
1143 response = sanitizeResponseIfPossible(WTFMove(response), ResourceResponse::SanitizationType::CrossOriginSafe);
1144 if (isSynchronous()) {
1145 m_synchronousLoadData->response = WTFMove(response);
1146 sendReplyToSynchronousRequest(*m_synchronousLoadData, entry->buffer(), { });
1147 cleanup(LoadResult::Success);
1148 return;
1149 }
1150
1151 bool needsContinueDidReceiveResponseMessage = isMainResource();
1152 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("didRetrieveCacheEntry: Sending WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse IPC (needsContinueDidReceiveResponseMessage=%d)", needsContinueDidReceiveResponseMessage);
1153 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveResponse { response, needsContinueDidReceiveResponseMessage });
1154
1155 if (needsContinueDidReceiveResponseMessage)
1156 m_cacheEntryWaitingForContinueDidReceiveResponse = WTFMove(entry);
1157 else {
1158 sendResultForCacheEntry(WTFMove(entry));
1159 cleanup(LoadResult::Success);
1160 }
1161}
1162
1163void NetworkResourceLoader::sendResultForCacheEntry(std::unique_ptr<NetworkCache::Entry> entry)
1164{
1165 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("sendResultForCacheEntry:");
1166#if ENABLE(SHAREABLE_RESOURCE)
1167 if (!entry->shareableResourceHandle().isNull()) {
1168 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidReceiveResource(entry->shareableResourceHandle()));
1169 return;
1170 }
1171#endif
1172
1173#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS) && !RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
1174 if (shouldLogCookieInformation(m_connection, sessionID()))
1175 logCookieInformation();
1176#endif
1177
1178 WebCore::NetworkLoadMetrics networkLoadMetrics;
1179 networkLoadMetrics.markComplete();
1180 networkLoadMetrics.requestHeaderBytesSent = 0;
1181 networkLoadMetrics.requestBodyBytesSent = 0;
1182 networkLoadMetrics.responseHeaderBytesReceived = 0;
1183 networkLoadMetrics.responseBodyBytesReceived = 0;
1184 networkLoadMetrics.responseBodyDecodedSize = 0;
1185
1186 sendBuffer(*entry->buffer(), entry->buffer()->size());
1187 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::DidFinishResourceLoad(networkLoadMetrics));
1188}
1189
1190void NetworkResourceLoader::validateCacheEntry(std::unique_ptr<NetworkCache::Entry> entry)
1191{
1192 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("validateCacheEntry:");
1193 ASSERT(!m_networkLoad);
1194
1195 // If the request is already conditional then the revalidation was not triggered by the disk cache
1196 // and we should not overwrite the existing conditional headers.
1197 ResourceRequest revalidationRequest = originalRequest();
1198 if (!revalidationRequest.isConditional()) {
1199 String eTag = entry->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::ETag);
1200 String lastModified = entry->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::LastModified);
1201 if (!eTag.isEmpty())
1202 revalidationRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfNoneMatch, eTag);
1203 if (!lastModified.isEmpty())
1204 revalidationRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfModifiedSince, lastModified);
1205 }
1206
1207 m_cacheEntryForValidation = WTFMove(entry);
1208
1209 startNetworkLoad(WTFMove(revalidationRequest), FirstLoad::Yes);
1210}
1211
1212void NetworkResourceLoader::dispatchWillSendRequestForCacheEntry(ResourceRequest&& request, std::unique_ptr<NetworkCache::Entry>&& entry)
1213{
1214 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("dispatchWillSendRequestForCacheEntry:");
1215 ASSERT(entry->redirectRequest());
1216 ASSERT(!m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect);
1217
1218 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) Executing cached redirect");
1219
1220 m_isWaitingContinueWillSendRequestForCachedRedirect = true;
1221 willSendRedirectedRequest(WTFMove(request), ResourceRequest { *entry->redirectRequest() }, ResourceResponse { entry->response() });
1222}

1229void NetworkResourceLoader::consumeSandboxExtensionsIfNeeded()
1230{
1231 if (!m_didConsumeSandboxExtensions)
1232 consumeSandboxExtensions();
1233}
1234
1235void NetworkResourceLoader::consumeSandboxExtensions()
1236{
1237 ASSERT(!m_didConsumeSandboxExtensions);
1238
1239 for (auto& extension : m_parameters.requestBodySandboxExtensions)
1240 extension->consume();
1241
1242 if (auto& extension = m_parameters.resourceSandboxExtension)
1243 extension->consume();
1244
1245 for (auto& fileReference : m_fileReferences)
1246 fileReference->prepareForFileAccess();
1247
1248 m_didConsumeSandboxExtensions = true;
1249}
1250
1251void NetworkResourceLoader::invalidateSandboxExtensions()
1252{
1253 if (m_didConsumeSandboxExtensions) {
1254 for (auto& extension : m_parameters.requestBodySandboxExtensions)
1255 extension->revoke();
1256 if (auto& extension = m_parameters.resourceSandboxExtension)
1257 extension->revoke();
1258 for (auto& fileReference : m_fileReferences)
1259 fileReference->revokeFileAccess();
1260
1261 m_didConsumeSandboxExtensions = false;
1262 }
1263
1264 m_fileReferences.clear();
1265}

1285static String escapeForJSON(String s)
1286{
1287 return s.replace('\\', "\\\\").replace('"', "\\\"");
1288}
1289
1290static String escapeIDForJSON(const std::optional<uint64_t>& value)
1291{
1292 return value ? String::number(value.value()) : String("None"_s);
1293}
1294
1295static String escapeIDForJSON(const std::optional<FrameIdentifier>& value)
1296{
1297 return value ? String::number(value->toUInt64()) : String("None"_s);
1298}
1299
1300static String escapeIDForJSON(const std::optional<PageIdentifier>& value)
1301{
1302 return value ? String::number(value->toUInt64()) : String("None"_s);
1303}

1305void NetworkResourceLoader::logCookieInformation() const
1306{
1307 ASSERT(shouldLogCookieInformation(m_connection, sessionID()));
1308
1309 auto* networkStorageSession = m_connection->networkProcess().storageSession(sessionID());
1310 ASSERT(networkStorageSession);
1311
1312 logCookieInformation(m_connection, "NetworkResourceLoader", reinterpret_cast<const void*>(this), *networkStorageSession, originalRequest().firstPartyForCookies(), SameSiteInfo::create(originalRequest()), originalRequest().url(), originalRequest().httpReferrer(), frameID(), pageID(), identifier());
1313}
1314
1315static void logBlockedCookieInformation(NetworkConnectionToWebProcess& connection, const String& label, const void* loggedObject, const WebCore::NetworkStorageSession& networkStorageSession, const URL& firstParty, const SameSiteInfo& sameSiteInfo, const URL& url, const String& referrer, std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID, std::optional<PageIdentifier> pageID, std::optional<uint64_t> identifier)
1316{
1317 ASSERT(NetworkResourceLoader::shouldLogCookieInformation(connection, networkStorageSession.sessionID()));
1318
1319 auto escapedURL = escapeForJSON(url.string());
1320 auto escapedFirstParty = escapeForJSON(firstParty.string());
1321 auto escapedFrameID = escapeIDForJSON(frameID);
1322 auto escapedPageID = escapeIDForJSON(pageID);
1323 auto escapedIdentifier = escapeIDForJSON(identifier);
1324 auto escapedReferrer = escapeForJSON(referrer);
1325
1326#define LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED(fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG_IF(networkStorageSession.sessionID().isAlwaysOnLoggingAllowed(), Network, "%p - %s::" fmt, loggedObject, label.utf8().data(), ##__VA_ARGS__)
1327#define LOCAL_LOG(str, ...) \
1328 LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED("logCookieInformation: BLOCKED cookie access for webPageID=%s, frameID=%s, resourceID=%s, firstParty=%s: " str, escapedPageID.utf8().data(), escapedFrameID.utf8().data(), escapedIdentifier.utf8().data(), escapedFirstParty.utf8().data(), ##__VA_ARGS__)
1329
1330 LOCAL_LOG(R"({ "url": "%{public}s",)", escapedURL.utf8().data());
1331 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "partition": "%{public}s",)", "BLOCKED");
1332 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "hasStorageAccess": %{public}s,)", "false");
1333 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "referer": "%{public}s",)", escapedReferrer.utf8().data());
1334 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "isSameSite": "%{public}s",)", sameSiteInfo.isSameSite ? "true" : "false");
1335 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "isTopSite": "%{public}s",)", sameSiteInfo.isTopSite ? "true" : "false");
1336 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "cookies": [])");
1337 LOCAL_LOG(R"( })");
1338#undef LOCAL_LOG
1339#undef LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED
1340}
1341
1342static void logCookieInformationInternal(NetworkConnectionToWebProcess& connection, const String& label, const void* loggedObject, const WebCore::NetworkStorageSession& networkStorageSession, const URL& firstParty, const WebCore::SameSiteInfo& sameSiteInfo, const URL& url, const String& referrer, std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID, std::optional<PageIdentifier> pageID, std::optional<uint64_t> identifier)
1343{
1344 ASSERT(NetworkResourceLoader::shouldLogCookieInformation(connection, networkStorageSession.sessionID()));
1345
1346 Vector<WebCore::Cookie> cookies;
1347 if (!networkStorageSession.getRawCookies(firstParty, sameSiteInfo, url, frameID, pageID, ShouldAskITP::Yes, ShouldRelaxThirdPartyCookieBlocking::No, cookies))
1348 return;
1349
1350 auto escapedURL = escapeForJSON(url.string());
1351 auto escapedPartition = escapeForJSON(emptyString());
1352 auto escapedReferrer = escapeForJSON(referrer);
1353 auto escapedFrameID = escapeIDForJSON(frameID);
1354 auto escapedPageID = escapeIDForJSON(pageID);
1355 auto escapedIdentifier = escapeIDForJSON(identifier);
1356 bool hasStorageAccess = (frameID && pageID) ? networkStorageSession.hasStorageAccess(WebCore::RegistrableDomain { url }, WebCore::RegistrableDomain { firstParty }, frameID.value(), pageID.value()) : false;
1357
1358#define LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED(fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG_IF(networkStorageSession.sessionID().isAlwaysOnLoggingAllowed(), Network, "%p - %s::" fmt, loggedObject, label.utf8().data(), ##__VA_ARGS__)
1359#define LOCAL_LOG(str, ...) \
1360 LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED("logCookieInformation: webPageID=%s, frameID=%s, resourceID=%s: " str, escapedPageID.utf8().data(), escapedFrameID.utf8().data(), escapedIdentifier.utf8().data(), ##__VA_ARGS__)
1361
1362 LOCAL_LOG(R"({ "url": "%{public}s",)", escapedURL.utf8().data());
1363 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "partition": "%{public}s",)", escapedPartition.utf8().data());
1364 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "hasStorageAccess": %{public}s,)", hasStorageAccess ? "true" : "false");
1365 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "referer": "%{public}s",)", escapedReferrer.utf8().data());
1366 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "isSameSite": "%{public}s",)", sameSiteInfo.isSameSite ? "true" : "false");
1367 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "isTopSite": "%{public}s",)", sameSiteInfo.isTopSite ? "true" : "false");
1368 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "cookies": [)");
1369
1370 auto size = cookies.size();
1371 decltype(size) count = 0;
1372 for (const auto& cookie : cookies) {
1373 const char* trailingComma = ",";
1374 if (++count == size)
1375 trailingComma = "";
1376
1377 auto escapedName = escapeForJSON(cookie.name);
1378 auto escapedValue = escapeForJSON(cookie.value);
1379 auto escapedDomain = escapeForJSON(cookie.domain);
1380 auto escapedPath = escapeForJSON(cookie.path);
1381 auto escapedComment = escapeForJSON(cookie.comment);
1382 auto escapedCommentURL = escapeForJSON(cookie.commentURL.string());
1383 // FIXME: Log Same-Site policy for each cookie. See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=184894>.
1384
1385 LOCAL_LOG(R"( { "name": "%{public}s",)", escapedName.utf8().data());
1386 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "value": "%{public}s",)", escapedValue.utf8().data());
1387 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "domain": "%{public}s",)", escapedDomain.utf8().data());
1388 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "path": "%{public}s",)", escapedPath.utf8().data());
1389 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "created": %f,)", cookie.created);
1390 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "expires": %f,)", cookie.expires.value_or(0));
1391 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "httpOnly": %{public}s,)", cookie.httpOnly ? "true" : "false");
1392 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "secure": %{public}s,)", cookie.secure ? "true" : "false");
1393 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "session": %{public}s,)", cookie.session ? "true" : "false");
1394 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "comment": "%{public}s",)", escapedComment.utf8().data());
1395 LOCAL_LOG(R"( "commentURL": "%{public}s")", escapedCommentURL.utf8().data());
1396 LOCAL_LOG(R"( }%{public}s)", trailingComma);
1397 }
1398 LOCAL_LOG(R"(]})");
1399#undef LOCAL_LOG
1400#undef LOCAL_LOG_IF_ALLOWED
1401}
1402
1403void NetworkResourceLoader::logCookieInformation(NetworkConnectionToWebProcess& connection, const String& label, const void* loggedObject, const NetworkStorageSession& networkStorageSession, const URL& firstParty, const SameSiteInfo& sameSiteInfo, const URL& url, const String& referrer, std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID, std::optional<PageIdentifier> pageID, std::optional<uint64_t> identifier)
1404{
1405 ASSERT(shouldLogCookieInformation(connection, networkStorageSession.sessionID()));
1406
1407 if (networkStorageSession.shouldBlockCookies(firstParty, url, frameID, pageID, ShouldRelaxThirdPartyCookieBlocking::No))
1408 logBlockedCookieInformation(connection, label, loggedObject, networkStorageSession, firstParty, sameSiteInfo, url, referrer, frameID, pageID, identifier);
1409 else
1410 logCookieInformationInternal(connection, label, loggedObject, networkStorageSession, firstParty, sameSiteInfo, url, referrer, frameID, pageID, identifier);
1411}
1412#endif

1429void NetworkResourceLoader::logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded(const NetworkCache::Cache::RetrieveInfo& info)
1430{
1431#if RELEASE_LOG_DISABLED
1432 UNUSED_PARAM(info);
1433#else
1434 auto duration = info.completionTime - info.startTime;
1435 if (duration < 1_s)
1436 return;
1437 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Took %.0fms, priority %d", duration.milliseconds(), info.priority);
1438 if (info.wasSpeculativeLoad)
1439 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Was speculative load");
1440 if (!info.storageTimings.startTime)
1441 return;
1442 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Storage retrieve time %.0fms", (info.storageTimings.completionTime - info.storageTimings.startTime).milliseconds());
1443 if (info.storageTimings.dispatchTime) {
1444 auto time = (info.storageTimings.dispatchTime - info.storageTimings.startTime).milliseconds();
1445 auto count = info.storageTimings.dispatchCountAtDispatch - info.storageTimings.dispatchCountAtStart;
1446 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Dispatch delay %.0fms, dispatched %lu resources first", time, count);
1447 }
1448 if (info.storageTimings.recordIOStartTime)
1449 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Record I/O time %.0fms", (info.storageTimings.recordIOEndTime - info.storageTimings.recordIOStartTime).milliseconds());
1450 if (info.storageTimings.blobIOStartTime)
1451 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Blob I/O time %.0fms", (info.storageTimings.blobIOEndTime - info.storageTimings.blobIOStartTime).milliseconds());
1452 if (info.storageTimings.synchronizationInProgressAtDispatch)
1453 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Synchronization was in progress");
1454 if (info.storageTimings.shrinkInProgressAtDispatch)
1455 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Shrink was in progress");
1456 if (info.storageTimings.wasCanceled)
1457 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("logSlowCacheRetrieveIfNeeded: Retrieve was canceled");
1458#endif
1459}

1461bool NetworkResourceLoader::isCrossOriginPrefetch() const
1462{
1463 auto& request = originalRequest();
1464 return request.httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Purpose) == "prefetch" && !m_parameters.sourceOrigin->canRequest(request.url());
1465}

1467#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1468void NetworkResourceLoader::startWithServiceWorker()
1469{
1470 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startWithServiceWorker:");
1471 ASSERT(!m_serviceWorkerFetchTask);
1472 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask = m_connection->createFetchTask(*this, originalRequest());
1473 if (m_serviceWorkerFetchTask) {
1474 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("startWithServiceWorker: Created a ServiceWorkerFetchTask (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64());
1475 return;
1476 }
1477
1478 serviceWorkerDidNotHandle(nullptr);
1479}
1480
1481void NetworkResourceLoader::serviceWorkerDidNotHandle(ServiceWorkerFetchTask* fetchTask)
1482{
1483 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("serviceWorkerDidNotHandle: (fetchIdentifier=%" PRIu64 ")", fetchTask ? fetchTask->fetchIdentifier().toUInt64() : 0);
1484 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_serviceWorkerFetchTask.get() == fetchTask);
1485 if (m_parameters.serviceWorkersMode == ServiceWorkersMode::Only) {
1486 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR("serviceWorkerDidNotHandle: Aborting load because the service worker did not handle the load and serviceWorkerMode only allows service workers");
1487 send(Messages::WebResourceLoader::ServiceWorkerDidNotHandle { }, identifier());
1488 abort();
1489 return;
1490 }
1491
1492 if (m_serviceWorkerFetchTask) {
1493 auto newRequest = m_serviceWorkerFetchTask->takeRequest();
1494 m_serviceWorkerFetchTask = nullptr;
1495
1496 if (m_networkLoad)
1497 m_networkLoad->updateRequestAfterRedirection(newRequest);
1498
1499 LOADER_RELEASE_LOG("serviceWorkerDidNotHandle: Restarting network load for redirect");
1500 restartNetworkLoad(WTFMove(newRequest));
1501 return;
1502 }
1503 start();
1504}
1505#endif
